Generally, we don't accept bare definitions without a minimal theory around them, so I'm marking this as `awaiting-author`. In this case, the minimal theory should include (at least)
- proofs of reflexivity, symmetry, and transitivity;
- proof of `Equidecomposable K s (e '' s)`, where `e` is an `AffineEquiv`;
- equidecomposable sets have the same cardinality;
- two finite sets of the same cardinality are equidecomposable.

